### 4. Collect planning seed

- **Type:** Simple skill execution
- **Intent:** Compile the required seed block for **`master-planner`** after a readable PRD artifact exists.
- **Inputs:** Approved PRD from §3 terminal result; optional title and **`Related`** hints from the opening message or prior developer answers.
- **Expected output:** A complete **`master-planner`** seed containing `Feature planning`, `PRD`, **`Parent: null`** (default), and optional **`Related`** entries for external PM / doc traceability.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - Required seed fields complete → continue to §5 to engage **`master-planner`**.
  - Title missing → ask the developer for the feature title, then resume this step.
  - **Default:** set **`Parent: null`** — **do not** run a parent **AskQuestion** for net-new delivery plans.
  - Developer explicitly names a non-null **`Parent`** slug or `@path` in the same message → use that value (exception only).
  - **`Related`** absent → record none and continue; optional external PM / doc links only when the developer supplies them.
  - **§3 Author PRD** with terminal approved result: optional one-line seed summary; **do not** wait for developer confirmation before §5.

#### External PM scope (`Related`)

Product and feature **scope** lives in external PM tools (JIRA, Trello, ClickUp, Asana, …). Sedea plans **anchor delivery** — they do not replace those backlogs.

- **`Parent: null`** is the default for new Master Plans and PR plans under this mission.
- Put external traceability in optional **`Related:`** seed lines (role + link or `@path`) when the developer provides them — for example `PM: https://…/PROJ-123` or `PRD: @path/to/doc`.
- **Forbidden:** treating Hub roadmap topics, **`top_level_topic`**, or plan-tree parents as the default intake model for new work (see **development-process.md** § *Root delivery plans vs legacy Hub parent intake*).

**Procedure**

1. Derive `Feature planning` title from the PRD heading or provided title.
2. Set `PRD` to the approved PRD path from §3 **`author-prd`** outputs (`prdRef` / `prdPath`).
3. Resolve **`Parent`**:
   - **Explicit developer override:** When the same message names a slug, `@path`, or absolute plan path for **`Parent`**, use that value.
   - **Default:** **`Parent: null`** — **no** parent **AskQuestion**.
4. Collect optional **`Related`** entries when the developer provides external PM or document links (see § *External PM scope*).
5. **Seed echo vs auto-chain:**
   - **§3 Author PRD** with terminal approved result: optional one-line seed summary; **do not** wait for developer confirmation before §5.
   - When title is set and **`Parent`** resolved per step 3, proceed to §5 without a separate approval gate; use **AskQuestion** only for missing title per **Next-step resolution**.
6. Preserve the seed for §5 **`master-planner`** handoff.

**Seed shape**

```text
Feature planning: "<title>"
PRD: <link or @path>
Parent: null
Related (optional):
- <role>: <link or @path>   # e.g. PM: JIRA/PROJ-123, PRD: @path
```

When an explicit developer override applies, replace the **`Parent:`** line with the resolved slug or `@path` instead of **`null`**.

### 5. Create Master Plan via agent

- **Type:** Agent engagement and handover
- **Intent:** Delegate Master Plan creation and §§1–5 drafting to a focused **Master Plan agent** while the **Squad Leader** keeps ownership of the overall `plan and deliver` protocol.
- **Inputs:** Complete seed from §4 (`Feature planning`, `PRD`, `Parent`, optional `Related`); Sedea always-apply rules; this mission plan; `development-process.md`; assigned skill `skills/master-planner/SKILL.md`.
- **Target agent role:** Master Plan agent
- **Assigned skill:** `.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/master-planner/SKILL.md`
- **Required rule context:** Sedea center always-apply rules, this mission plan, `development-process.md`, planning target resolution rule, and the `master-planner` skill.
- **Expected output:** Child agent result with `status: success` or `partial`, `outputs.masterPlanPath`, `outputs.masterPlanSlug`, `outputs.complexityBand`, `outputs.complexityScore`, `outputs.continuationOwner`, `outputs.continuationStatus`, `outputs.activeLanes`, `outputs.openLedgerEntries`, `outputs.spawnedPlans`, `outputs.remainingTasks`, and any recommended next action.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - Child result `success` with Master Plan path and low/medium complexity plus active continuation ownership → continue to status acknowledgement and ledger tracking; the **master-planner** lane owns downstream route prompts and inline decomposition.
  - Child result `success` with high complexity → acknowledge **Route §6 → Delivery phases** recommendation on the **Master Plan agent** lane (high band triggers phase decomposition via **`delivery-phases`** / **`phase-planner`**, not a §6 withhold); keep the **Master Plan agent** lane open; do not foreground decomposition from the **Squad Leader** lane.
  - Child result `partial` with usable Master Plan path → surface gaps and continue only if they do not block routing.
  - Child result `failure`, `aborted`, `abandoned`, or no plan path → USER_CHECKPOINT — retry, revise seed, or abandon.

**Procedure**

1. Compile the **Master Plan agent** input from the §4 seed.
2. **Spawn preflight (mandatory before emit).** Read **`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/master-planner/SKILL.md`** frontmatter **`inputs`** and **`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Universal spawn preflight*. Build the spawn **`inputs`** object with **exact** keys:

   | `inputs` key | Source |
   |--------------|--------|
   | `seedBlock` | Full §4 seed block text (`Feature planning`, `PRD`, `Parent`, optional `Related`) |
   | `featurePlanningTitle` | Title from §4 / PRD heading — **not** `featurePlanning` |
   | `prdRef` | Approved PRD link or `@path` from §3 **`author-prd`** outputs |
   | `parent` | When §4 seed has **`Parent: null`**, set spawn **`"parent": "null"`** (JSON string sentinel). Otherwise resolved slug, `@path`, or absolute plan path. **Forbidden:** JSON `null` in spawn `inputs.parent` — **`master-planner`** frontmatter declares **`type: string`**. Sidecar **`parent: null`** is unrelated to spawn wire encoding. |
   | `related` | Array from §4 `Related` entries, or `[]` when none |

   **Seed vs spawn (binding):** **`Parent: null`** in the §4 seed block is semantic (root delivery plan). The spawn line must still include **`"parent": "null"`** as a **string** in **`inputs`** — not JSON null and not omission of the key. See **`planner/SKILL.md`** § *Wire encoding — nullable `parent`* and **`skills/README.md`** § *Universal spawn preflight* row **1b**.

   **Stop** and surface a one-line fix list when any required key is missing, renamed, or nested under the wrong parent key. Do **not** emit `mission_control_spawn_agent` until preflight passes.

   Set **`name`** to `MP-{featurePlanningTitle}` (or PRD title) and **`description`** to a one-line Master Plan drafting summary — not generic "Planner" / "Child agent" placeholders alone (README § *Universal spawn preflight*; rule **50** § *Lane title prefix conventions*).

3. Emit exactly one `mission_control_spawn_agent` request for the **Master Plan agent** using the `master-planner` skill path, a **new** `correlationId`, dispatch-unique `slug`, topic-specific **`name`** / **`description`**, and the preflight **`inputs`** from step 2. See **`planner/SKILL.md`** § *Spawn contract* for a valid example line and failure modes.
4. Emit **`mission_control_spawn_agent`**, announce that the **Squad Leader** is waiting because later protocol steps need the produced plan path and complexity result, and open a **next-step resume** structured choice (**#external-wait**) before ending the turn.
5. Stop protocol execution until Mission Control delivers `mission_control_send_agent_result` for the same `correlationId`.
6. Validate that returned outputs include a readable Master Plan path, complexity band, continuation owner/status, and ledger-shaped arrays (`activeLanes`, `openLedgerEntries`, `spawnedPlans`, `remainingTasks`) before continuing.

### 6. Acknowledge Master Plan status

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Avoid duplicate continuation prompts by pausing the **Squad Leader** while the **Master Plan agent** owns the planning lane.
- **Inputs:** Master Plan agent result: plan path, slug, complexity band, complexity score, child status, continuation owner/status, and any downstream notification requirement.
- **Expected output:** One status acknowledgement from the **Squad Leader**; no route menu.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - Master Plan agent reports active continuation ownership → acknowledge status and enter a resumable wait state.
  - Master Plan agent reports terminal success and no remaining **planning** tasks → continue **§7** then **§8**; do **not** propose **`resolved`** dispatch from §6 alone (planning complete ≠ ship complete).
  - Master Plan agent reports failure or no usable plan path → USER_CHECKPOINT — retry, revise seed, switch PRD source, or abandon.
  - Downstream agent result arrives → resume only when the result requires mission-level action.

**Procedure**

1. Read the Master Plan agent result.
2. If the result includes a usable plan path and indicates the **Master Plan agent** owns continuation, acknowledge status only.
3. **Forbidden on the Squad Leader lane:** Do **not** present **Delivery phases**, **PR breakdown**, **Caveats**, or §6 decomposition **AskQuestion** menus here. Those routes live on the **master-planner** child lane only (**`planner/SKILL.md`** Step 7 — recap + structured choice per **`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`** and **`skills/README.md`** § *Recap, structured choice, act*). The leader does **not** run **`delivery-phases`** or **`pr-breakdown`** inline or via spawn from §6.
4. Pause the **Squad Leader** in a resumable wait state for downstream notifications.

### 7. Maintain planning closure ledger

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Track **planning-phase** completion while downstream planning agents own plan-building continuation. Ship-phase tracking is **§8**.
- **Inputs:** Master Plan agent result; every later downstream child result; plan path and child plan paths reported by downstream agents; continuation status; active lane identifiers; remaining task lists.
- **Expected output:** Updated closure ledger, status acknowledgement, continued wait, or dispatch resolution proposal.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - New phase or PR plan is spawned → add it to the closure ledger as open.
  - Downstream child result reports active continuation → acknowledge status and keep that lane open.
  - Downstream child result reports terminal completion for a registered phase or PR plan → mark that ledger entry closed.
  - Any child result reports failure, aborted, or abandoned → mark the ledger blocked and USER_CHECKPOINT — retry, revise scope, accept partial resolution, or abandon.
  - Planning ledger has no open or blocked entries and every planning lane is terminal → continue **§8** (do **not** propose **`resolved`** here if ship work remains).

**Planning ledger rules**

- The **Squad Leader** owns **planning** closure accounting; downstream agents own planning choices and child spawning.
- Every phase or PR plan spawned from the Master Plan tree must have an explicit **planning** ledger entry.
- The **Squad Leader** must receive terminal closure for every open **planning** entry before treating planning as complete.
- A plan entry may close as completed, deferred, abandoned, or out of scope, but the closing status must be explicit.
- Silence, missing metadata, or an unreported lane is not completion.
- When a PR plan child reports `readyForImplementation` in planning `outputs`, record planning-handoff readiness on the **planning** ledger only. Planning vs ship signals and §8 phase rules: [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/30_planning-target-resolution.mdc`](../../rules/30_planning-target-resolution.mdc) § *Planning readiness vs ship*; §8 registration: §8 *Register or refresh* below.
- **Depth-first indexed rows:** track each parent-list index with `listed` | `active` | `ship-complete` (or `deferred` / `abandoned`). The next **`new-plan`** expand on that parent is allowed only when **30_planning-target-resolution** § *Depth-first expansion eligibility* passes — for **Delivery phases** lists, the prior phase index must be **ship-complete** per that rule (including explicit `deferred` / `abandoned` closures); for **`### PR list`**, follow parsed **`### Sequencing`** stages. Do not treat planning-terminal child lanes alone as unlocking the next index.
- **Spawn-chain ship-complete:** when child terminals bubble **`outputs.prShipComplete`** or **`outputs.phaseShipComplete`** through the planning tree (see **`missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Upstream ship-complete notification*), register the matching index as **`ship-complete`** on the planning ledger and acknowledge — the **Master Plan agent** owns **`expand-eligible`** / **`expand-next-eligible`** on its lane; the Squad Leader does not re-run expand. When spawn bubble-up is missing, treat as a **ship skill contract gap** (§8 *Automation completeness*) — do not substitute manual **Ship recap**.

**Procedure**

1. Initialize the planning ledger when the Master Plan agent reports a plan path and continuation ownership.
2. Register each downstream phase plan, PR plan, or agent lane when a child reports it was spawned or made active.
3. On each downstream result, update the matching planning entry by correlation id, plan path, or reported slug.
4. Acknowledge updates without presenting planning route choices from the **Squad Leader** lane.
5. When the planning ledger has no open/blocked work and all planning lanes are terminal, continue **§8**.

### 8. Ship cadence ledger and dispatch resolution gates

- **Type:** Finish/stop logic
- **Intent:** Close the gap between **objectives** (implementation → PR → deploy → reconcile) and **Squad Leader** protocol. The Squad Leader **tracks** detached ship work and **gates** `mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`; it does **not** spawn ship skills from this section.
- **Inputs:** Planning ledger state from §7; developer messages on the leader lane; **`coding-session`** child `outputs` (especially `developerApprovedImplementation`, `targetPlanPath` after the worktree-open gate); explicit developer status when ship runs on other lanes.
- **Expected output:** Updated **ship ledger** per PR plan; status acknowledgement; **`mission_control_propose_dispatch_resolution`** only when gates below allow.
- **Next-step resolution:**
  - No ship row yet, planning complete → USER_CHECKPOINT — close dispatch planning-only vs keep ship active on detached lanes.
  - Ship row open → keep dispatch **active** (auto-advance ack); acknowledge phase updates; do **not** propose **`resolved`**.
  - All ship rows **closed** (or explicitly deferred/abandoned per row) → propose dispatch resolution per **`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/4_mission.mdc`**.
  - Developer requests wrap-up with open ship → propose **`partial`** or **`abandoned`** with explicit remaining work in the JSON `summary`.

USER_CHECKPOINT — approve dispatch resolution when planning and ship gates allow.

